WEBVTT

00:02.770 --> 00:04.140
Ohh, yeah!

00:04.138 --> 00:06.808
♪ Powerpuff girls
fighting crime ♪

00:06.807 --> 00:09.377
♪ To save the world
before bedtime ♪

00:09.377 --> 00:11.877
♪ Here's the time to shine
when you're fighting crime ♪

00:11.879 --> 00:13.649
♪ Power it up ♪
♪ Who's got the power? ♪

00:13.647 --> 00:15.107
♪ We got the power ♪

00:15.116 --> 00:17.316
♪ Breaking through the wall,
gonna do it all ♪

00:17.318 --> 00:19.518
♪ We don't quit ♪
♪ Who's got the power? ♪

00:19.520 --> 00:21.150
♪ We got the power ♪

00:21.155 --> 00:23.685
Oh! Yeah!

00:29.414 --> 00:32.454
Whoo-hoo!
Halloween!

00:32.451 --> 00:36.191
[ All talking indistinctly ]

00:37.622 --> 00:40.262
[ Doorbell rings ]

00:40.258 --> 00:42.188
Well, hello.

00:42.194 --> 00:43.594
All: Trick or treat.

00:43.595 --> 00:44.955
Now, who do we have here?

00:44.963 --> 00:47.203
Let's see --
a spooky skeleton...

00:47.199 --> 00:48.429
Meh.

00:48.433 --> 00:50.473
...a penguin...
Mm-hmm.

00:50.469 --> 00:53.369
...and, um,
the Queen of England?

00:53.372 --> 00:54.672
[ Buzzer ]
Mm.

00:54.673 --> 00:56.173
Happy Halloween.

00:56.174 --> 00:59.784
I can't believe nobody's
getting my costume.

00:59.778 --> 01:02.878
I mean,
I'm Ada Lovelace,

01:02.881 --> 01:05.351
one of the greatest
mathematicians of all time.

01:05.349 --> 01:06.620
I hear ya, sister.

01:06.618 --> 01:08.648
Nobody's getting my costume,
either.

01:08.653 --> 01:10.453
Everyone thinks
I'm a skeleton.

01:10.455 --> 01:12.115
Wait, you're not?

01:12.124 --> 01:17.534
No. I'm Sergeant Bones
with my trusty laser mop.

01:17.529 --> 01:19.499
Pew! Pew!
Pew, pew, pew, pew!

01:19.498 --> 01:21.458
Please,
that's not a character.

01:21.466 --> 01:23.866
That's just stuff you
found in the -- Pew. Pew!

01:23.869 --> 01:27.139
Ah, gross.
Quit it, Buttercup.

01:27.139 --> 01:29.669
Hey, Bubbs,
what's our candy status?

01:29.674 --> 01:30.914
Not good.

01:30.909 --> 01:33.809
Bubbles,
you're depleting our reserves.

01:33.812 --> 01:36.712
We got to hit up more houses
if we want a stockpile.

01:36.715 --> 01:38.975
Well, according to my list,

01:38.984 --> 01:41.024
we've been to every house
in the neighborhood

01:41.019 --> 01:42.819
except that one.

01:42.821 --> 01:45.891
[ Thunder crashes, wolf howls ]

01:45.891 --> 01:48.321
I don't know.
It looks kind of scary.

01:48.326 --> 01:50.386
Eh, what could go wrong?

01:50.395 --> 01:51.825
[ All screaming ]

01:51.830 --> 01:54.230
How dare you
steal all my candy.

01:55.734 --> 01:58.204
Buttercup, the sign said,
"Take one."

01:58.203 --> 02:01.843
What? Oh, I thought it meant
take one basket.

02:01.840 --> 02:03.840
Oh, don't even try
pulling that one.

02:03.842 --> 02:05.342
You knew very well
what it meant.

02:05.343 --> 02:09.013
Please, Mr. Very Strong
Yellow Pumpkin Monster.

02:09.014 --> 02:11.954
Excuse you?!
I am not a pumpkin monster.

02:11.950 --> 02:13.280
I'm a spaghetti squash,

02:13.285 --> 02:15.515
the most neglected squash
of Halloween.

02:15.520 --> 02:17.590
Oh, I hate those pumpkins
so much.

02:17.589 --> 02:19.359
It's always pumpkin pie,
pumpkin latte,

02:19.357 --> 02:20.857
take your pumpkin to prom!

02:20.859 --> 02:23.359
Wait,
so you're not a pumpkin?

02:23.361 --> 02:25.761
Of course I'm not!

02:25.764 --> 02:27.104
You three
are about to find out

02:27.099 --> 02:30.199
just how scary
a spaghetti squash can be.

02:30.202 --> 02:33.742
I'm going to crush you into
next year's Halloween candy.

02:33.738 --> 02:35.738
[ Laughs evilly ]

02:35.740 --> 02:38.640
Yeah right.
You're not that scary.

02:38.643 --> 02:41.243
What? Yes, I am.

02:41.246 --> 02:42.906
No one is scarier than me.

02:42.914 --> 02:47.654
Okay. Well, then if that's true,
nothing should scare you --

02:47.652 --> 02:49.722
not even the scariest story
on the planet,

02:49.721 --> 02:51.891
which we happen to know,
right girls?

02:51.890 --> 02:53.590
Uh, yeah.
We do?

02:53.592 --> 02:55.062
Shh.

02:55.060 --> 02:57.890
Look, if we can scare you
with one of our stories,

02:57.896 --> 02:59.396
will you let us go?

02:59.397 --> 03:00.897
Hmm, okay.

03:00.899 --> 03:04.099
But if it's not scary,
it's crush city.

03:04.102 --> 03:07.402
Leave this
to Sergeant Bones.

03:07.405 --> 03:12.405
Our story begins
on a dark and stormy night,

03:12.410 --> 03:16.580
The Night of The Living Bread.

03:16.581 --> 03:18.481
Grains.

03:18.483 --> 03:20.653
Grains.

03:20.652 --> 03:23.092
Grains.

03:24.756 --> 03:28.286
Well, it may be
a zombie bread apocalypse,

03:28.293 --> 03:31.533
but at least we're spending it
together as a family.

03:31.530 --> 03:34.000
[ Sigh ]
Except for Buttercup,

03:33.999 --> 03:36.969
who took on all of those
pumpernickels by herself

03:36.968 --> 03:39.098
so we could escape.

03:39.104 --> 03:42.974
She truly was
the coolest.

03:42.974 --> 03:46.984
Don't you mean
<i> is</i> the coolest?

03:46.978 --> 03:48.178
Buttercup?
Buttercup?

03:48.180 --> 03:50.880
Buttercup,
I'm so glad you're here.

03:50.882 --> 03:54.182
The bread --
they've surrounded the house,

03:54.186 --> 03:59.056
and all of my plans
are complicated and annoying.

03:59.057 --> 04:01.957
Typical Blossom.
Relax, kid.

04:01.960 --> 04:04.360
I got a chopper on its way
to take us to safety.

04:04.362 --> 04:06.302
We just got to make it
to the roof.

04:06.298 --> 04:08.898
Good, 'cause the walking bread
are coming.

04:08.900 --> 04:12.800
Correction, Bubbs.
They're already here.

04:12.804 --> 04:15.144
Grains.

04:15.140 --> 04:17.570
Grains, wah.

04:17.576 --> 04:20.305
Ugh, grains.

04:20.312 --> 04:22.312
Tee hee hee.

04:22.314 --> 04:23.714
Watch out guys.

04:23.715 --> 04:27.545
If they bite you,
you turn into one of them.

04:27.552 --> 04:29.322
Grains.

04:29.321 --> 04:32.021
Yeah, go, Buttercup. Huh!
Hyah! [ Screaming ]

04:32.023 --> 04:35.093
Yeah.
Oh, hi girls.

04:35.093 --> 04:37.893
Hi, Zombie Mayor.
Look out.

04:42.100 --> 04:45.840
Hey, super gal pals,
I'm gluten-free.

04:45.837 --> 04:47.997
It's more expensive.

04:48.006 --> 04:51.506
Doesn't matter.
Still makes good croutons.

04:53.845 --> 04:56.745
Mmm,
a taste of the upper-crust.

04:56.748 --> 04:58.848
Ha, good one, Buttercup.

04:58.850 --> 05:03.250
[ Groans ] Mojo
is the most evil banana bread.

05:03.255 --> 05:07.155
Heh, sorry, buddy.
Butter-luck next time.

05:10.462 --> 05:12.862
Okay, we'll be safe now.

05:12.864 --> 05:14.304
[ Moaning ]

05:14.299 --> 05:16.699
Blossom,
you've been bitten.

05:16.701 --> 05:21.541
I'm an essential part
of the food pyramid.

05:21.539 --> 05:26.379
I'm sorry, old friend.

05:26.378 --> 05:28.108
[ Screams ]

05:28.113 --> 05:30.083
Aah!

05:30.081 --> 05:32.781
Come on, Bubbs.
We have to get to the chopper.

05:32.784 --> 05:35.054
Coming.

05:35.053 --> 05:38.623
Wow, Buttercup,
you're the coolest.

05:38.623 --> 05:40.063
I know.

05:40.058 --> 05:41.518
Whee!

05:42.627 --> 05:45.257
We're gonna make it.

05:45.263 --> 05:49.073
Hello, Buttercup.
Thanks for in-biting me.

05:49.067 --> 05:53.467
Ugh, enough.
Introducing Dracula now?

05:53.471 --> 05:54.671
It's a twist.

05:54.673 --> 05:57.113
It's a hack move
and not scary.

05:57.108 --> 06:00.178
Wait. I happen to know
a thing or two about scary.

06:00.178 --> 06:03.108
[ Scoffs ] You? The girl
dressed like a peacock lady?

06:03.114 --> 06:04.784
Ugh, whatever.
Just listen.

06:04.783 --> 06:09.093
This story is sure to make
your vines curl with fear.

06:09.087 --> 06:12.917
I call this one Blossomstein.

06:12.924 --> 06:15.494
Ah, my dearest Jared.

06:15.493 --> 06:18.493
Long and cold has been
the winter in my heart

06:18.496 --> 06:21.796
since you shuffled off
this mortal coil.

06:21.800 --> 06:24.370
Hey, who you talking to?
[ Squawks ]

06:24.369 --> 06:26.339
Be gone, foul raven.

06:26.338 --> 06:30.108
B-Gor, is my experiment
prepared?

06:30.108 --> 06:34.278
Yes, it is, Master.

06:34.279 --> 06:36.979
Man, what's up with
all this lightning?

06:36.981 --> 06:39.951
[ Squawk ]

06:39.951 --> 06:44.691
Oh, Jared, we will be together
again soon, my love,

06:44.689 --> 06:48.389
once I bring you
back to life.

06:48.393 --> 06:51.833
Geez, Bloss. Pretty desperate
to go after a dead guy.

06:51.830 --> 06:54.130
[ Squawks ]
I don't know.

06:54.132 --> 06:57.632
I think zombie love
is pretty romantic.

06:57.635 --> 07:03.135
[ Clears throat ] Let us
commence with the experiment.

07:03.141 --> 07:05.641
[ Machine powers on,
electricity crackles ]

07:06.978 --> 07:08.478
[ Ding! ]

07:16.254 --> 07:17.924
[ Coughing ]

07:17.922 --> 07:21.722
Jared?
Jared, can you hear me?

07:21.726 --> 07:23.886
Blossom.

07:23.895 --> 07:26.425
Jared, you're alive.

07:26.431 --> 07:30.331
Oh, my sweet,
speak of the love between us.

07:30.335 --> 07:33.365
Blossom good.

07:33.371 --> 07:35.511
Well, he's got the basic concept
down.

07:35.507 --> 07:36.537
[ Doorbell rings ]

07:36.541 --> 07:39.341
Oh, sweet! Pizza's here.
[ Squawks ]

07:39.344 --> 07:40.784
Hello?

07:40.779 --> 07:44.009
Yeah, I've hear you've been
working on building a monster,

07:44.015 --> 07:48.445
and as a spokesperson of the
Townsylvania Home Owners Association,

07:48.453 --> 07:52.793
I'm here to tell you
that's strictly against code.

07:52.791 --> 07:55.591
[ Angry mob shouting ]

07:55.593 --> 07:58.093
Hey, he's not a monster.

07:58.096 --> 08:02.396
He's a highly intelligent,
sensitive, charming human being.

08:02.400 --> 08:06.270
[ Chewing ]
Nachos good.

08:06.271 --> 08:10.641
Look, it's the monster,
and he's got nachos.

08:12.377 --> 08:14.477
Fire bad.

08:14.479 --> 08:15.709
Get him.

08:15.713 --> 08:17.083
[ All shouting ]

08:17.081 --> 08:19.821
No, no, stop, stop.

08:19.818 --> 08:21.248
Aah!

08:21.252 --> 08:23.052
You're tracking in mud!

08:23.054 --> 08:26.394
[ Shouting continues ]

08:26.391 --> 08:28.721
Aah,
you're staining the carpet.

08:28.726 --> 08:31.456
[ Shouting continues ]

08:34.399 --> 08:37.929
Nooooo!

08:37.936 --> 08:41.566
Everything is a mess!

08:41.573 --> 08:43.472
Sorry if it got
too dark there.

08:43.475 --> 08:45.635
A messy house?

08:45.643 --> 08:48.283
Do you girls even know
what scary is?

08:48.279 --> 08:52.919
I do.
Get ready to get spooky.

08:52.917 --> 08:56.517
I call this one
"A Gourd to Remember."

08:56.521 --> 09:00.261
Narrator: Tony was a spaghetti
squash who had it all --

09:00.258 --> 09:05.128
a great job in the big city,
a bicycle with ten speeds,

09:05.129 --> 09:07.659
and an adorable puppy dog.
Woof, woof.

09:07.665 --> 09:12.125
But sometimes,
life doesn't go as you planned.

09:12.136 --> 09:14.336
You're fired, Tony.

09:14.339 --> 09:18.409
Everybody knows pumpkins are
what's in for Halloween now.

09:21.446 --> 09:24.606
Whoa. Ohh.

09:24.616 --> 09:26.746
[ Horn blares ]

09:28.453 --> 09:31.623
Narrator: It seemed
that Tony had lost it all,

09:31.623 --> 09:36.063
but luckily his best friends
came to the rescue.

09:36.060 --> 09:38.460
Tony, you have to stop
letting other people

09:38.463 --> 09:40.633
define happiness for you.

09:40.632 --> 09:44.732
Come on, girl, you got to
get your groove back.

09:44.736 --> 09:47.296
Does someone need to
get their groove back?

09:47.305 --> 09:50.465
Because a giant pumpkin monster
is attacking.

09:50.475 --> 09:52.635
If someone has a vendetta
against pumpkins,

09:52.644 --> 09:54.814
now is their time
to get revenge.

09:54.812 --> 09:57.152
That's right, girls.

09:57.148 --> 10:00.648
It's time for this gourd
to get back in the game.

10:00.652 --> 10:03.522
[ Growls ]

10:03.521 --> 10:06.761
Narrator: But when Tony
faced his biggest fear,

10:06.758 --> 10:11.658
he found love
in the most unexpected place.

10:11.663 --> 10:16.073
And so Tony was finally able
to open up his heart

10:16.067 --> 10:18.727
and spill out
his true feelings.

10:18.736 --> 10:21.696
Bubbles, that was the opposite
of scary.

10:21.706 --> 10:22.936
That was actually --

10:22.941 --> 10:24.841
Romantic?

10:24.842 --> 10:28.912
It's true. I love pumpkins.
That's why I drive them away.

10:28.913 --> 10:33.353
The one thing that I'm really
scared of is...my feelings.

10:33.351 --> 10:36.221
Bubbles, was this your plan
all along?

10:36.220 --> 10:39.360
Yeah, I mean,
who could hate pumpkins?

10:39.357 --> 10:41.457
You know what?
You're right.

10:41.459 --> 10:43.729
Here. You should
take all the candy.

10:43.728 --> 10:46.298
I got to go see about
a jack-o-lantern.

10:46.297 --> 10:49.267
You go, Tony.
Get that Gourd.

10:49.267 --> 10:50.867
Mojo Jojo: Trick or treat.

10:50.868 --> 10:56.038
Surrender all your puny candy
to Mojo Jojo.

10:56.040 --> 10:59.210
Great.
Another Ada Lovelace?

10:59.210 --> 11:01.710
Finally, someone gets it.

11:04.315 --> 11:05.815
♪ Powerpuff girls
fighting crime ♪

11:05.817 --> 11:08.377
♪ Saving the world
before bedtime ♪

11:08.386 --> 11:11.046
♪ Battling evil toe-to-toe ♪

11:11.055 --> 11:15.055
♪ Saving the day,
a Powerpuff goal ♪
